Leveling for xp at 60 is a lot easier than at 55 or 56, even without Epic. The reason is you get better debuffs, less resists, more efficient(most important part)! spells and can kill monsters which only have a lvl difference of like 2 levels higher for xp.<br>
<br>
I would put in 10% in AA till 58 and then as you wish.<br>
<br>
The main reason for 10% is, if you die even with a resurrection you lose 0 AA point exp. And 10% is just not very noticeable when xping <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also if you continue with 10% from 56 to 60 you will make approx. 7-8 AA (56 will be about 1.5, 57 about 1.75, 58 about 2, 59 about 4) points which is very nice and allows you to go into the Class category immediately <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
But most of all do what is good for you and not what we think would be good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
